arfs. Moreover, we found that the\npseudo-equivalent width (pEW) of the H$\\alpha$ and Ca ii infrared triplet more\noften triggers automatic detections of long-term variations than the TiO index,\ndifferential line width, chromatic index, or radial velocity. This is in line\nwith our comparison of the median relative amplitudes of the different\nindicators. For stars that trigger our automatic detection, this leads to the\nhighest amplitude variation in R$^{\\prime}_{\\rm HK}$, followed by\npEW(H$\\alpha$), pEW(Ca ii IRT), and the TiO index.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Dec 2022 08:39:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-08"}
