{"id":"2212.03571","submitter":"Ebrahim Ghorbani","authors":"Maryam Abdi, Ebrahim Ghorbani","title":"Minimum algebraic connectivity and maximum diameter: Aldous--Fill and\n  Guiduli--Mohar conjectures","comments":"23 pages, new version, minor corrections","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO math.PR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Aldous and Fill (2002) conjectured that the maximum relaxation time for the\nrandom walk on a connected regular graph with $n$ vertices is\n$(1+o(1))\\frac{3n^2}{2\\pi^2}$. A conjecture by Guiduli and Mohar (1997)\npredicts the structure of graphs whose algebraic connectivity $\\mu$ is the\nsmallest among all connected graphs whose minimum degree $\\delta$ is a given\n$d$. We prove that this conjecture implies Aldous--Fill conjecture for odd $d$.\nWe pose another conjecture on the structure of $d$-regular graphs with minimum\n$\\mu$, and show that this also implies Aldous--Fill conjecture for even $d$. In\nthe literature, it has been noted empirically that graphs with small $\\mu$ tend\nto have a large diameter. Guiduli asked if the cubic graphs with maximum\ndiameter have algebraic connectivity smaller than all others. We investigate\nthe interplay between the graphs with maximum diameter and those with minimum\nalgebraic connectivity. We show that the answer to Guiduli problem in its\ngeneral form, that is for $d$-regular graphs for every $d\\ge3$ is negative. We\ntry to come up with an asymptotic formulation of the problem. We prove that for\n$d=3,4$, $d$-regular graphs with asymptotic maximum diameter have\nasymptotically smallest $\\mu$. It is shown that this fails for $d$-regular\ngraphs with $d\\ge5$ as well as graphs with $\\delta=d$ with $d\\ge4$. We\nconjecture that $d$-regular graphs (or graphs with $\\delta=d$) that have\nasymptotically smallest $\\mu$, should have asymptotically maximum diameter. The\nabove results rely heavily on our understanding of the structure as well as\noptimal estimation of the algebraic connectivity of graphs with asymptotic\nmaximum diameter. As another by-product, we prove that the minimum algebraic\nconnectivity of $d$-regular graphs of order $n$ or graphs with $\\delta=d$ is\n$\\Theta(d/n^2)$, and also settle Aldous--Fill conjecture for graphs with\nasymptotic maximum diameter.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Dec 2022 11:10:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 4 Feb 2023 19:49:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-07"}
